headline: U.S. state visit yields record 150 billion pounds of investment, UK says
summary: LONDON (Reuters) -U.S. President Donald Trump's state visit to Britain has generated 150 billion pounds ($204.87 billion) of inward investment, the British government said on Wednesday citing its own data which compiled new and previously announced pledges.  The figure, which Britain said was the largest commercial investment package generated by any state visit, was announced after Trump's day of royal pageantry and ahead of the political leg of the visit, when he will meet Prime Minister Keir Starmer.

headline: Starmer hails £150bn US tie-up amid ‘vassal state’ criticism
summary: Sir Keir Starmer has unveiled a £150bn investment in Britain as the former deputy prime minister Sir Nick Clegg warned that the UK was becoming a “vassal state” of America.
